Perfect ‚Äî that error dump tells me Maven (or Gradle) isn‚Äôt recognizing your Spring Boot dependencies (especially the core + YAML libs).
Let‚Äôs fix this cleanly üí™


---

‚úÖ Root Cause

Your compiler says:

org.springframework.context.annotation.* not found ‚Üí means spring-context not in classpath.

org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.* not found ‚Üí means spring-beans missing.

org.yaml.snakeyaml.* not found ‚Üí means snakeyaml not included.


So this isn‚Äôt a Java code problem ‚Äî it‚Äôs your missing dependencies.


---

‚úÖ Step 1: Check You‚Äôre in a Spring Boot Project

In pom.xml (if using Maven), ensure you have:

<parent>
    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-parent</artifactId>
    <version>3.3.2</version> <!-- or your preferred version -->
</parent>

<dependencies>
    <!-- Spring Boot Core -->
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter</artifactId>
    </dependency>

    <!-- Web Starter (for REST controllers) -->
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-web</artifactId>
    </dependency>

    <!-- YAML parser -->
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.yaml</groupId>
        <artifactId>snakeyaml</artifactId>
        <version>2.2</version>
    </dependency>

    <!-- Optional: Lombok -->
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.projectlombok</groupId>
        <artifactId>lombok</artifactId>
        <optional>true</optional>
    </dependency>

    <!-- Test dependencies -->
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-test</artifactId>
        <scope>test</scope>
    </dependency>
</dependencies>

<build>
    <plugins>
        <plugin>
            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
            <artifactId>spring-boot-maven-plugin</artifactId>
        </plugin>
    </plugins>
</build>

Then run:

mvn clean install

or, if using Gradle:

gradle clean build


---

‚úÖ Step 2: Verify Imports in YamlConfig.java

Make sure your imports look exactly like this:

package com.example.travel.config;

import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;
import org.springframework.context.annotation.Bean;
import org.springframework.context.support.PropertySourcesPlaceholderConfigurer;
import org.yaml.snakeyaml.Yaml;

import java.io.InputStream;
import java.util.Map;


---

‚úÖ Step 3: Verify File Location

Ensure the path is correct:

src/main/java/com/example/travel/config/YamlConfig.java

(lowercase config, not Config ‚Äî Java package names should be lowercase).


