---

Would you like me to now connect these dropdowns and radio buttons to the Spring Boot backend with YAML-driven values (the main.yml + multiple field YAMLs setup)?















You‚Äôre absolutely right ‚úÖ ‚Äî you don‚Äôt have an app.module.ts, because your app is standalone (Angular 10.9.2 standalone setup using AppComponent + ApplicationConfig).
Thanks for catching that ‚Äî we‚Äôll fix it without adding a module file.

Let‚Äôs fix all three errors properly inside your existing standalone setup:


---

‚ö†Ô∏è The Errors You Mentioned

1. ‚ÄúNeither ngFor directive nor CommonModule was imported‚Äù
‚Üí You need to import CommonModule in every standalone component that uses *ngFor or *ngIf.


2. ‚ÄúRouterOutlet is not a known element‚Äù
‚Üí Import RouterOutlet in your AppComponent (which you already do, but we‚Äôll double-check).


3. ‚ÄúCan‚Äôt bind to formGroup since it isn‚Äôt a known property of form‚Äù
‚Üí You must import ReactiveFormsModule in your standalone component where the form is defined.




---

‚úÖ Here‚Äôs how to fix everything

üü¢ app.ts

Make sure your root component imports RouterOutlet and CommonModule (you already had this mostly right).

import { Component } from '@angular/core';
import { Router, RouterOutlet } from '@angular/router';
import { CommonModule } from '@angular/common';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [RouterOutlet, CommonModule],
  templateUrl: './app.html',
  styleUrls: ['./app.css']
})
export class AppComponent {
  menuOpen = false;

  constructor(private router: Router) {}

  toggleMenu() {
    this.menuOpen = !this.menuOpen;
  }

  navigateTo(path: string) {
    this.menuOpen = false;
    this.router.navigate([path]);
  }
}


---

üü¢ travell.ts (your New Travel form component)

Here‚Äôs the corrected version that includes all needed imports:

import { Component } from '@angular/core';
import { CommonModule } from '@angular/common';
import { FormBuilder, FormGroup, ReactiveFormsModule, Validators } from '@angular/forms';
import { TravelService } from '../travel';
import { Router } from '@angular/router';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-travell',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [CommonModule, ReactiveFormsModule],
  templateUrl: './travell.html',
  styleUrls: ['./travell.css']
})
export class TravellComponent {
  travelForm!: FormGroup;

  domains = ['Finance', 'HR', 'IT'];
  clusters = ['Cluster A', 'Cluster B', 'Cluster C'];
  subclusters = ['Sub-1', 'Sub-2'];
  cluster1s = ['Cluster1-X', 'Cluster1-Y'];
  hods = ['HOD1', 'HOD2'];
  cities = ['Bangalore', 'Chennai', 'Mumbai'];
  travelTypes = ['Domestic', 'International'];
  travelClasses = ['Economy', 'Business'];
  types = ['Official', 'Personal'];

  constructor(private fb: FormBuilder, private travelService: TravelService, private router: Router) {
    this.travelForm = this.fb.group({
      uid: ['', Validators.required],
      name: ['', Validators.required],
      lineManager: ['', Validators.required],
      domain: ['', Validators.required],
      cluster: ['', Validators.required],
      subcluster: ['', Validators.required],
      cluster1: ['', Validators.required],
      hod: ['', Validators.required],
      originCity: ['', Validators.required],
      destinationCity: ['', Validators.required],
      startDate: ['', Validators.required],
      endDate: ['', Validators.required],
      travelType: ['', Validators.required],
      travelClass: ['', Validators.required],
      type: ['', Validators.required],
      purpose: ['', [Validators.required, Validators.maxLength(250)]]
    });
  }

  submitForm() {
    if (this.travelForm.valid) {
      this.travelService.addTravel(this.travelForm.value);
      alert('Travel request submitted successfully!');
      this.travelForm.reset();
      this.router.navigate(['travel-details']);
    } else {
      alert('Please fill all required fields.');
    }
  }
}


---

